    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Centre Hospitalier Universitaire Dijon</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The current management of ischemic stroke is based on different strategies that may be
      combined: intravenous thrombolysis in a stroke ICU, intravenous thrombolysis in a
      telemedicine procedure, endovascular thrombectomy. Given this now rich therapeutic arsenal,
      it seems necessary to evaluate practices in local care in the field and the impact of these
      on the prognosis of ischemic stroke victims. The aim of this observational study is to
      compare these different care practices without interfering with the choice of strategy.

      A blood sample will also be taken at different times to study the value of growth
      differentiation factors (GDF) 8, 11 and 15, and Brain-derived Neurotrophic Factor as
      prognostic biomarkers
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
